cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses meta-learning methods for improving the training and meta-test-time performance of deep learning models. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural networks (cs.NE). Given the focus on deep learning and optimization algorithms, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI and cs.CV. The paper also discusses transfer-risk bounds and geometric structures, which are more commonly studied in the context of statistical learning theory and optimization, further supporting the inclusion of cs.LG and cs.AI.
